               <p>GEORGE GREEN. I live in <placeName id="t18340904-39-crimeloc216">Long-alley</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18340904-39-crimeloc216" type="placeName" value="Long-alley"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18340904-39-crimeloc216" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340904-39-off214 t18340904-39-crimeloc216"></join>; the prisoner lodged with my mother. On the 6th of December, I saw my watch safe at five minutes before eight o'clock in the morning - the prisoner was then sitting on the bed putting on his trowsers - I dropped asleep again, and when I awoke, he was gone, and my watch too - it was not more than three minutes after eight o'clock when I missed him - my brother was in the same room, but he was in bed - I afterwards saw the prisoner in Shoreditch - I tapped him on the shoulder, and asked him to come back to my mother's, which he did, and I gave him into custody - he said he had sold the watch in Bristol.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340904-39-person314">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BRUFF
